:R-HSA-191650  a            obo:GO_0008150 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Src is believed to suppress gap junction communication by phosphorylating Cx43. The kinases c-Src (Giepmans et al. 2001; Sorgen et al. 2004), PKc (Lin et al. 2003) and MAPK (Mograbi et al. 2003) play an essential role in the phosphorylation of Cx which leads to its degradation. c-Src appears to associate with and phosphorylate Cx43 leading to closure of gap junctions. Evidence suggests that v-src may activate MAPK, which in turn phosphorylates Cx43 on serine sites leading to channel gating (Zhou et al. 1999)." ;
        rdfs:label          "Regulation of gap junction activity" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Matthews, L, 2007-04-17 13:54:37" , "Authored: Gilleron, J, Segretain, D, Falk, MM, 2007-01-03 12:23:09" , "GOC:reactome_curators" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-191650" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-157858/R-HSA-157858> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

